      "stem_html": "<p>Dimethyl butynedioate undergoes a Diels–Alder reaction with (2<i>E</i>,4<i>E</i>)-2,4-hexadiene. Show the structure and stereochemistry of the product.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ3NWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--82154f93cd596e1cff2167948ac0e9bcc71750a7/OChem_14_EC_035.jpg\" alt=\"The condensed formula of compound has a 4-carbon chain. C 2 is triple-bonded to C3. C1 and C4 are carbonyl groups each bonded to methoxy groups, C 5, C 6, and C 10 are all double-bonded to oxygen atoms.\">",
